<@UCT80F90E> I think you need to include some high-res images of your 'wall' of decks to give folks a real view into what this entails.

Alright folks, time to discuss reviews
We're doing it in seven parts. The first five are by guild, indicated by Watermark. The next two are Guildless cards. Some authors have already laid claim to some guilds

-Golgari [Dean]
-Boros
-Izzet [Christian had indicated interest in this or Dimir]
-Dimir
-Selesnya [Matt]
-Guildless pt.1 (White, Blue, Black) [Mason had indicated interest in this or Dimir]
-Guildless pt.2 (Red, Green, Artifacts, Lands)

If I've missed people, my apologies. There's usually a lot of interest in these so it's kinda first-come-first-served

AS A REMINDER: You're not reviewing every single card, just the stuff that could be EDH relevant. Please refer to the style guide pinned to this channel for formatting and examples. I promise the answers to a lot of questions are in there, such as the one I expect we'll be getting a lot, "When are these being published?" ASAP, hopefully. Next week, as the articles are submitted, most likely in addition to our normal articles. I don't have a particular order but I do wanna put at least one out per day, so don't wait until Thursday to write your review.

Let the set review hunger games begin
